'''''Ben Hur Live''''' is a 2009 stage adaptation of [[Lew Wallace]]'s novel ''[[Ben-Hur: A Tale of the Christ]]''. Produced by [[Franz Abraham]] with music and narration by [[Stewart Copeland]], it premi<U+00E8>red on 17 September 2009 at the [[The O2 arena (London)|O2 Arena]] in London, the first date of its European tour.

The show's dialogue is in [[Latin]] and [[Aramaic]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/stage/theatreblog/2009/sep/14/ben-hur-live|title=Ben Hur Live leaves little to the imagination|last=Espiner|first=Mark|date=14 September 2009|work=guardian.co.uk|publisher=Guardian News and Media|accessdate=18 September 2009}}</ref> and it includes a [[sea battle]] and [[gladiatorial combat]], as well as the [[chariot race]] for which ''Ben Hur'' is famous. It is based primarily on the book as its source material rather than the [[Ben-Hur (1959 film)|Academy Award-winning adaptation]] which starred [[Charlton Heston]].

== Reception ==
After its London premi<U+00E8>re, it received mixed reviews from theatre critics.<ref name="PressRev">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/arts_and_culture/8262536.stm|title=Ben Hur Live: press views|date=18 September 2009|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|accessdate=18 September 2009}}</ref>

